http://www.thehindu.com/news/national/other-states/Ajit-Jogi-files-defamation/article13982585.ece

Congress leader Ajit Jogi on Monday filed a defamation suit against a national English daily in a local court here, alleging that his image had been “maligned” through a “baseless and fake” story that he and his son Amit had “fixed” a by-poll in 2014 to ensure victory for the BJP.The case was filed under Sections 499 (defamation), 500 (punishment for defamation), 501 (printing or engraving matter known to be defamatory), 502 (sale of printed or engraved substance containing defamatory matter) and 34 of IPC in the court of Judicial Magistrate First Class Udaylaxmi Parmar, Jogi’s lawyer Ashok Sharma said.Mr. Jogi, a former Chief Minister of Chhattisgarh, also recorded his statement in the court on Monday.-PTI